        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3869060653" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7739390379034477434">This is the 6th book in the series and I think it is the best by far. This story is about the steps that a person who was abused 22 years earlier attempted to prevent the individual responsible who had powerful wealth/family and political ties from being nominated for the Supreme Court. The way the story was constructed from the introduction of the incident until the time of the Senate hearing will show the reader how difficult this was to accomplish. The actions that Zack took for his client an</span>
  <span id="freeText7739390379034477434" style="display:none">This is the 6th book in the series and I think it is the best by far. This story is about the steps that a person who was abused 22 years earlier attempted to prevent the individual responsible who had powerful wealth/family and political ties from being nominated for the Supreme Court. The way the story was constructed from the introduction of the incident until the time of the Senate hearing will show the reader how difficult this was to accomplish. The actions that Zack took for his client and the team that supported him showed co-operation at its best. <br /><br />It also highlighted what steps those in political power would take to allow the confirmation to succeed. The final scene in the Senate chambers and the events which occurred after will keep you guessing how this will all turn out.<br /><br />It also brings to mind the type of happenings during Brett Kavanaugh's hearings which took place right after Donald Trump became President.<br /><br />If you enjoy details of how things get accomplished, then you must read this book. It will keep you going right through the end. I couldn't put it down until I finished it. You won't either.</span>
