<span id="freeTextContainer8933951352069979866">Supreme Betrayal (A Zachary Blake Legal Thriller Book 6) by Mark M. Bello is a riveting legal thriller that pulls from today&apos;s headlines. When a young woman Hayley, who has always stayed on the straight and narrow decides to go to a party, things go awry quickly after she has one too many drinks. She is brutally attacked. The attacker, Oliver Wilkinson is later a Presidential nominee for the Supreme Court. It&apos;s twenty years later, and Hayley simply cannot let that take place. Told from alternati</span>
  <span id="freeText8933951352069979866" style="display:none">Supreme Betrayal (A Zachary Blake Legal Thriller Book 6) by Mark M. Bello is a riveting legal thriller that pulls from today's headlines. When a young woman Hayley, who has always stayed on the straight and narrow decides to go to a party, things go awry quickly after she has one too many drinks. She is brutally attacked. The attacker, Oliver Wilkinson is later a Presidential nominee for the Supreme Court. It's twenty years later, and Hayley simply cannot let that take place. Told from alternative points of view, this is a well-written book that resonates with the current climate of the Me Too movement and more. Full of detail and highly skilled and accurate writing, this is a great legal thriller that engrossed from the beginning pages. A fantastic addition to this exceptional series, this one is highly recommended.</span>
