        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4025192461" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4035550906571379357">[English review + Reseña en español]<br/><br/><i>Supreme Betrayal (A Zachary Blake Legal Thriller)</i> by Mark M. Bello<br/>Grand Publications, 2020<br/>279 pages<br/>Fiction / Legal thriller.<br/><br/>In 1997, during a teenagers party, the Wilkinson&apos;s son and his best friend tried to sexually abuse Hayley, then a minor. Twenty-three years later, the nation is reeling after two Republican presidencies whose measures have been draconian. The only Supreme Court judge who maintained the fragile balance between the parties has just resigned</span>
  <span id="freeText4035550906571379357" style="display:none">[English review + Reseña en español]<br /><br /><i>Supreme Betrayal (A Zachary Blake Legal Thriller)</i> by Mark M. Bello<br />Grand Publications, 2020<br />279 pages<br />Fiction / Legal thriller.<br /><br />In 1997, during a teenagers party, the Wilkinson's son and his best friend tried to sexually abuse Hayley, then a minor. Twenty-three years later, the nation is reeling after two Republican presidencies whose measures have been draconian. The only Supreme Court judge who maintained the fragile balance between the parties has just resigned and, among the five names that are being considered to succeed him, stands out that of young Judge Oliver Wilkinson, a radical conservative who seems to openly advocate the lack of justice and the total imbalance in favor of the extreme right. Zachary Blake, the billionaire and famed human rights and social justice lawyer, makes it his goal to stop Wilkinson's rise, seeing in him a huge threat to democracy and justice. When Hayley (now married with children) learns of Oliver's opportunity of success, she decides to fight so that her attacker does not get his way as if nothing ever happened.<br /><br />This legal thriller, inspired by and dedicated to the <i>Me Too</i> movement, is part of a series of novels starring attorney Zachary Blake. Written by a lawyer with extensive professional experience both in the legal field and in fiction writing, the novel tells of a very current struggle in which the characters and the situations they face feel totally logical and real. I think that the dialogues, the investigation, the intrigue and the action will completely satisfy fans of the genre.<br /><br />This is a highly recommended book for those who enjoy the genre of legal suspense and want to understand why reporting and fighting are important even when some misconduct seems like a thing of the past.<br /><br />-------<br /><br /><i>Supreme Betrayal (A Zachary Blake Legal Thriller)</i>, de Mark M. Bello<br />Grand Publications, 2020<br />279 páginas<br />Ficción / Suspenso legal.<br /><br />En 1997, durante una fiesta de adolescentes, el hijo de los Wilkinson y su mejor amigo intentaron abusar sexualmente de Hayley, entonces menor de edad. Veintitrés años después la nación está tambaleante tras dos presidencias republicanas cuyas medidas han sido draconianas. El único juez de la Suprema Corte que mantenía el frágil equilibrio entre los partidos acaba de renunciar y, entre los cinco nombres que se barajan para sucederlo, destaca el del joven Juez Oliver Wilkinson, un conservador radical que parece abogar abiertamente por la falta de justicia y el desequilibrio total en favor de la extrema derecha. Zachary Blake, el multimillonario y afamado abogado defensor de los derechos humanos y la justicia social, se pone como meta detener el ascenso de Wilkinson, pues ve en él una amenaza enorme a la democracia y a la justicia. Cuando Hayley (ahora casada y con hijos) se entera de las posibilidades de triunfo de Oliver, decide luchar para que su agresor no se salga con la suya.<br /><br />Esta novela de suspenso legal, inspirada por, y dedicada al movimiento <i>Me Too</i>, es parte de una serie de novelas cuyo protagonista es el abogado Zachary Blake. Escrita por un abogado con gran experiencia profesional tanto en el ámbito legal como en el de la escritura de ficción, la novela cuenta una lucha por demás actual en la que los personajes y las situaciones que enfrentan se sienten totalmente lógicas y reales. Creo que los diálogos, la investigación, la intriga y la acción dejarán totalmente satisfechos a los amantes del género.<br /><br />Este es un libro muy recomendable para aquellos que disfruten el género del suspenso legal y quieran comprender por qué la denuncia y la lucha son importantes aun cuando las faltas cometidas parezcan cosa del pasado.<br /></span>
