<div id="review_4031902681" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4031902681" />
    <a title="Mariel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/99593899-mariel"><img alt="Mariel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1563615007p2/99593899.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4031902681?book_show_action=true">Jun 03, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mariel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mariel" href="/user/show/99593899-mariel">Mariel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/99593899-mariel?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/99593899-mariel?shelf=crime">crime</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/99593899-mariel?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4031902681" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3128607585858609298">Supreme Betrayal (A Zachary Blake Legal Thriller Book 6) by Mark M. Bello<br/><br/>I received a copy and am voluntarily leaving a review.<br/><br/>Hayley Lawson remembers only too well the events of the dreadful night. Oliver Wilkinson comes from a prosperous neighbourhood, and along with his brother are entitled, rich boys. Their house is known as the place to be. Accompanied by a friend, he corners Hayley in an upstairs bathroom in his home, full of drunken partygoers and attempts to rape her.<br/><br/>Over twenty years la</span>
  <span id="freeText3128607585858609298" style="display:none">Supreme Betrayal (A Zachary Blake Legal Thriller Book 6) by Mark M. Bello<br /><br />I received a copy and am voluntarily leaving a review.<br /><br />Hayley Lawson remembers only too well the events of the dreadful night. Oliver Wilkinson comes from a prosperous neighbourhood, and along with his brother are entitled, rich boys. Their house is known as the place to be. Accompanied by a friend, he corners Hayley in an upstairs bathroom in his home, full of drunken partygoers and attempts to rape her.<br /><br />Over twenty years later, married and successful, caring for a family of her own, she still suffers from the horror of the assault. She reassures herself she can place the nightmare behind her and concentrate on furthering her career, until Oliver is selected to be part of the Supreme Court Justice. She has no choice but to expose him as a sexual predator and confront her past.<br /><br />Hayley is portrayed as an amazing, dynamic woman who publicly opposes the perpetrator of an alleged crime. As the novel unfolds, it becomes clear how involved this entire process is. Mark M. Bello has an intense descriptive style and exploits the theatrical performances of the lawyers in a courtroom battle. This book develops into much more than a battle of banter between defendant and prosecutor. <br /><br />I can’t imagine Hayley’s state of mind. Oliver becomes more confident in himself reaching the position he craves and thinks he deserves. In return, I became more and more concerned that he could succeed. He was a wealthy man; I dreaded him being able to corrupt the politicians by buying their silence.<br /><br />The pathway through the book creates intrigue, as we speculate what to expect next! The reader is hooked, drawn through the book, left chewing on the ending scene. From the offset, there is a moment of intense politics which is a fundamental part of the tale. Stay with it because it unfolds and leads to an intricate web of deceit that does not disappoint. Oliver is a despicable character. Bello has fashioned the qualities we detest in society, completely into this one man and as a reader, we demand justice for Hayley because we recognize the distinction between right and wrong. No one wants evil to win over good.<br /><br />I did not foresee this conclusion but I love it all the more for providing a fascinating twist. I held at the back of my mind several possibilities in the way it could pan out, but this was one I had not considered, thankyou Mark M. Bello for the welcome surprise!<br /><br />I rate Supreme Betrayal <b>5 out of 5 stars.</b></span>
  <a data-text-id="3128607585858609298" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


