<div id="review_3972850482" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3972850482" />
    <a title="Grymm Gevierre" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/110261611-grymm-gevierre"><img alt="Grymm Gevierre" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1616326387p2/110261611.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3972850482?book_show_action=true">Apr 29, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Grymm Gevierre" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Grymm Gevierre" href="/user/show/110261611-grymm-gevierre">Grymm Gevierre</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3972850482" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13600594347674082972">This is my second Mark Bello book, and I feel like I probably need to get on the bandwagon here and grab some more. This is the 6th book and is stronger than the last I read. The writing, plot, characters, are all a step up from the last book. Bello is definitely growing stronger as a writer, and that’s saying something because the last book I read was pretty solid. What makes these stories stand out, I think, is that Bello pulls from real-life experience and then expands on it with fiction. It </span>
  <span id="freeText13600594347674082972" style="display:none">This is my second Mark Bello book, and I feel like I probably need to get on the bandwagon here and grab some more. This is the 6th book and is stronger than the last I read. The writing, plot, characters, are all a step up from the last book. Bello is definitely growing stronger as a writer, and that’s saying something because the last book I read was pretty solid. What makes these stories stand out, I think, is that Bello pulls from real-life experience and then expands on it with fiction. It makes the stories realistic and the characters believable. <br /><br />This particular story follows Hayley, a victim of sexual assault, and her mission to prevent her abuser from gaining a position of power. Of course, our beloved lawyer, Zackary Blake, is in the center of the fight and leads Hayley on her adventure; but the story really isn’t his. It’s Hayley’s. You can feel the emotions that drive her. When she teams up with Blake you can feel the hope and determination pour off the page. Highly recommend it, this is a stellar book. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13600594347674082972" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


