<span id="freeTextContainer5603285576648561060">Hayleigh Larson is the victim of a sexual assault that occurred 22 years ago and Oliver Wilson is the perpetrator and now the president’s nominee for a vacant seat on the Supreme Court, which he has aspired to his entire career. Hayleigh can&apos;t let this happen, but Oliver will stop at nothing to ensure his seat on the court. This is going to be one hell of a fight for Hayleigh, will she succeed in her endeavour to bring Oliver Wilson down and get justice? With the help of legal attorney Zachary B</span>
  <span id="freeText5603285576648561060" style="display:none">Hayleigh Larson is the victim of a sexual assault that occurred 22 years ago and Oliver Wilson is the perpetrator and now the president’s nominee for a vacant seat on the Supreme Court, which he has aspired to his entire career. Hayleigh can't let this happen, but Oliver will stop at nothing to ensure his seat on the court. This is going to be one hell of a fight for Hayleigh, will she succeed in her endeavour to bring Oliver Wilson down and get justice? With the help of legal attorney Zachary Blake she may just prevail.<br /><br />I found Supreme Betrayal to be a stomach-churning and compelling legal thriller that I didn't want to put down. Bello’s books are always extremely well-written, and in Supreme Betrayal he immerses the reader into the world of the rich and powerful, showing just how far these people will go to protect their secrets. I was drawn in from the first chapter, and enjoyed every twist and turn as the plot progressed. A definite 5 star rating from me.</span>
