<span id="freeTextContainer18312563155306491525">Supreme Betrayal<br/>By<br/>Mark M Bello<br/><br/>My Review:<br/>Recently I got my hands on a legal thriller written by Mark M Bello. Supreme Betrayal is the sixth installment in A Zachary Blake Legal Thriller Book series. Hayley Larson isn&apos;t a party girl. Everyone used to tease her that she follows her parents&apos; rules. So, Hayley went to the Wilkinson party i.e. against her parents rules. She didn&apos;t know that she will become the victim of sexual assault at the hands of Oliver Wilkinson and his best friend Shane Marbury.</span>
  <span id="freeText18312563155306491525" style="display:none">Supreme Betrayal<br />By<br />Mark M Bello<br /><br />My Review:<br />Recently I got my hands on a legal thriller written by Mark M Bello. Supreme Betrayal is the sixth installment in A Zachary Blake Legal Thriller Book series. Hayley Larson isn't a party girl. Everyone used to tease her that she follows her parents' rules. So, Hayley went to the Wilkinson party i.e. against her parents rules. She didn't know that she will become the victim of sexual assault at the hands of Oliver Wilkinson and his best friend Shane Marbury. Fast forward to 2020, Hayley's husband called her downstairs to watch the news related to the vacant seat on the Supreme Court. Out of six candidates, Oliver Wilkinson is the President's nominee for the vacant seat on the Supreme Court. Oliver doesn't have a good reputation in the eyes of attorney Zachary Blake and Hayley Larson. Can they stop a sexual predator to rule the seat of the highest court? Story is intense. It has an intelligent plot. It involves politics too. It is an engaging read and a kinda story that's gonna stay in the reader's head for a long time. Mark's entire series is amazing. Thriller lovers should pick the entire series and I am sure they will have a great time reading it.<br /><br />My Rating: 5/5</span>
