<span id="freeTextContainer4359824102525226938">Supreme Betrayal is another interesting legal thriller in the series. In 1997, a party was thrown by Oliver Wilkinson and his brother Jared. Oliver and Jared are the sons of wealthy parents. Oliver had always got what he wanted. Parties with wild sex, drugs, alcohol, etc is what he do whenever his parents are on a trip. At the recent party at his mansion, he saw an attractive girl Hayley coming out of the master bathroom. <br/><br/>Oliver and his best friend Shane Marbury assaulted Hayley. She tried to se</span>
  <span id="freeText4359824102525226938" style="display:none">Supreme Betrayal is another interesting legal thriller in the series. In 1997, a party was thrown by Oliver Wilkinson and his brother Jared. Oliver and Jared are the sons of wealthy parents. Oliver had always got what he wanted. Parties with wild sex, drugs, alcohol, etc is what he do whenever his parents are on a trip. At the recent party at his mansion, he saw an attractive girl Hayley coming out of the master bathroom. <br /><br />Oliver and his best friend Shane Marbury assaulted Hayley. She tried to seek justice but no action was ever taken against Oliver. Now, in 2020, Hayley was stunned to see the news that Judge Oliver Wilkinson has been tapped by President Stephen Golding to fill the vacancy left by the retirement of Associate Justice Noah Fitzgerald. Hayley and her husband Joel approached a trial lawyer Zachary Blake to stop Oliver. Will they be able to stop Wilkinson? <br /><br />This is a great story with a wonderful plot. The detail with which Mark writes his story plots are amazing. It gives the readers a great idea about the criminal world. Title of the book couldn't have been better than this. Cover photo is nice. Once again, I am impressed with Mark's writing. Get your hands on this page-turner story now.</span>
