<span id="freeTextContainer16163168408013220497">𝑻𝒊𝒕𝒍𝒆: Supreme Betrayal<br/>𝑨𝒖𝒕𝒉𝒐𝒓: Mark M Bello<br/><br/>𝑴𝒚 𝑹𝒆𝒗𝒊𝒆𝒘: <br/>In Supreme Betrayal, Hayley and Joel Schultz are happily married and they are the parents of two kids. Eighteen years ago, when Hayley and Joel were students, they met at a coffee shop at U of M. Joel put efforts in courting Hayley and soon she fell in love with him. Hayley opened up to Joel and told him about the assault that happened to her at the Wilkinson party. <br/><br/>Oliver Wilkinson, the one who assaulted Hayley, is the President’s nominee fo</span>
  <span id="freeText16163168408013220497" style="display:none">𝑻𝒊𝒕𝒍𝒆: Supreme Betrayal<br />𝑨𝒖𝒕𝒉𝒐𝒓: Mark M Bello<br /><br />𝑴𝒚 𝑹𝒆𝒗𝒊𝒆𝒘: <br />In Supreme Betrayal, Hayley and Joel Schultz are happily married and they are the parents of two kids. Eighteen years ago, when Hayley and Joel were students, they met at a coffee shop at U of M. Joel put efforts in courting Hayley and soon she fell in love with him. Hayley opened up to Joel and told him about the assault that happened to her at the Wilkinson party. <br /><br />Oliver Wilkinson, the one who assaulted Hayley, is the President’s nominee for a vacant seat on the Supreme Court, the position he has coveted his entire career. Can Hayley let this happen? Can she let Oliver become the justice of the highest court? Hayley and Joel asked for help from high profile attorney Zachary Blake who also doesn't want to see Oliver on the seat of the Supreme Court. <br /><br />The way the story started is amazing. Narration is strong. The moment I started reading this book, I was pulled inside the story. Mark's story plots are superb and it would be awesome to see movies on his story plots. If you are a fan of reading legal thrillers then Mark's stories are what you should pick.<br /><br />𝑴𝒚 𝑹𝒂𝒕𝒊𝒏𝒈: 5/5</span>
