        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4398037703" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4375441382248504951"><strong>Excellent story about the struggle between justice and power</strong><br/><br/>This book is not for light or superficial reading. It is a dense thriller that makes us evoke complex images, reflect, whose reading captures all the attention from the beginning making it very difficult to put the book down. Money always means power, and power can give you just about anything you want, like a Supreme Court date ... unless someone very brave isn&apos;t afraid to go head-to-head with the greats and stands in your way. Hayley&apos;</span>
  <span id="freeText4375441382248504951" style="display:none"><strong>Excellent story about the struggle between justice and power</strong><br /><br />This book is not for light or superficial reading. It is a dense thriller that makes us evoke complex images, reflect, whose reading captures all the attention from the beginning making it very difficult to put the book down. Money always means power, and power can give you just about anything you want, like a Supreme Court date ... unless someone very brave isn't afraid to go head-to-head with the greats and stands in your way. Hayley's determination and courage to keep Oliver from being named, and how Zach and his team support her despite previously known dangers and injustices, is admirable. A brilliant and well-documented legal thriller that you won't want to stop reading until you've savored and tasted the last chapter. Excellent reading for people who are fond of studying the law, human rights, and everything related to justice processes.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4375441382248504951" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

